zlog
------------------------------------------
zlog is a reliable, high-performance, thread safe, flexible, clear-model, pure
C logging library.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.4-1
  libzlog-devel-1.2.18-1bl1
  libzlog1-1.2.18-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cmake-3.28.3-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  ninja-1.12.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/HardySimpson/zlog

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/HardySimpson/zlog/archive/1.2.18.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack zlog-1.2.18-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./zlog-1.2.18-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/zlog-1.2.18-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/zlog-1.2.18-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libzlog1-1.2.18-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libzlog-devel-1.2.18-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(zlog)
  /usr/bin/zlog-chk-conf.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/zlog.README
  /usr/share/doc/zlog/Changelog
  /usr/share/doc/zlog/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/zlog/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/zlog/TODO

(libzlog1)
  /usr/bin/cygzlog-1.dll

(libzlog-devel)
  /usr/include/zlog.h
  /usr/lib/libzlog.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/zlog.pc

